Bronx, Westchester Criminal Defense Attorney









Few decisions in life are as critical as your choice of a criminal defense attorney. When your future is at stake, you need a skilled courtroom advocate with the experience 
      to present an effective defense for you.
Since graduating from New York Law School in 1972, Marvin Ray Raskin has been an active trial practitioner in the criminal 
      court system — first as an Assistant District Attorney and special prosecutor and in private practice since 1977.
Marvin is often consulted by civil and criminal attorneys and the public at large for advice in the fields of criminal investigations, law enforcement interrogations, and grand-jury subpoenas.
Mr. Raskin's areas of concentration are criminal defense and legal and judicial disciplinary matters.









